### EventLedger — interactive API demo
###
### Prerequisites
###   docker compose up --build
###   OR run both services locally (Gateway :8080, Account :8081)
###
### Fresh demo (recommended before interviews):
###   docker compose down -v && docker compose up --build
###   OR delete local gateway.db / account.db before dotnet run
###
### Run order: A → B → C top to bottom. Sections D (Swagger), E (observability), and F (graceful degradation) are optional.
###
### Tools: VS Code REST Client, Visual Studio, or Rider — click "Send Request"
### Alternative: import demo/EventLedger.postman_collection.json into Postman
###
### Expected HTTP status codes (Gateway POST /events)
###   201 — new event applied (first submission of an eventId)
###   200 — idempotent replay (Idempotency-Replay: true; steps 1–2 return 200 on re-run)
###   400 — validation error
###   429 — inbound rate/concurrency limit (default: 300 writes/min/IP)
###   503 — Account Service unavailable (event NOT stored)
###
### Resiliency (for reviewers)
###   Inbound:  concurrency bulkhead + per-client write rate limit
###   Outbound: Polly circuit breaker → retry (jitter) → timeout on Account Service

@gatewayUrl = http://localhost:8080
@accountUrl = http://localhost:8081
@accountId = acct-demo-001
@creditEventId = evt-credit-1001
@debitEventId = evt-debit-1002
@outOfOrderAcct = acct-demo-out-of-order

###############################################################################
# A. Happy path — credit, debit, idempotency, reads
###############################################################################

### 0a. Gateway health (exempt from inbound bulkhead)
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/health

### 0b. Account Service health
GET {{accountUrl}}/health

### 1. Submit CREDIT (+150.00) -> 201 Created (200 on re-run), creates account
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/events
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "eventId": "{{creditEventId}}",
  "accountId": "{{accountId}}",
  "type": "CREDIT",
  "amount": 150.00,
  "currency": "USD",
  "eventTimestamp": "2026-06-26T16:00:00Z",
  "metadata": { "source": "demo", "note": "opening deposit" }
}

### 2. Submit DEBIT (40.00, type=DEBIT) -> 201 Created (200 on re-run)
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/events
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "eventId": "{{debitEventId}}",
  "accountId": "{{accountId}}",
  "type": "DEBIT",
  "amount": 40.00,
  "currency": "USD",
  "eventTimestamp": "2026-06-26T16:05:00Z"
}

### 3. Idempotency replay — same credit event -> 200 + Idempotency-Replay: true
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/events
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "eventId": "{{creditEventId}}",
  "accountId": "{{accountId}}",
  "type": "CREDIT",
  "amount": 150.00,
  "currency": "USD",
  "eventTimestamp": "2026-06-26T16:00:00Z",
  "metadata": { "source": "demo", "note": "opening deposit" }
}

### 4. Get one event by id (Gateway local DB — works even if Account Service is down)
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/events/{{creditEventId}}

### 5. List events for account (ordered by eventTimestamp)
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/events?account={{accountId}}

### 6. Balance -> expect 110.00 (150 - 40)
GET {{accountUrl}}/accounts/{{accountId}}/balance

### 7. Account detail + recent transactions
GET {{accountUrl}}/accounts/{{accountId}}

###############################################################################
# B. Out-of-order arrival — submit reverse chronological, balance still correct
###############################################################################

### 8a. Out-of-order: T3 CREDIT +50 (latest timestamp first) -> 201 (200 on re-run)
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/events
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "eventId": "evt-ooo-t3",
  "accountId": "{{outOfOrderAcct}}",
  "type": "CREDIT",
  "amount": 50.00,
  "currency": "USD",
  "eventTimestamp": "2026-06-26T18:00:00Z"
}

### 8b. Out-of-order: T2 DEBIT 30 (type=DEBIT) -> 201 (200 on re-run)
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/events
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "eventId": "evt-ooo-t2",
  "accountId": "{{outOfOrderAcct}}",
  "type": "DEBIT",
  "amount": 30.00,
  "currency": "USD",
  "eventTimestamp": "2026-06-26T17:00:00Z"
}

### 8c. Out-of-order: T1 CREDIT +100 (earliest timestamp last) -> 201 (200 on re-run)
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/events
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "eventId": "evt-ooo-t1",
  "accountId": "{{outOfOrderAcct}}",
  "type": "CREDIT",
  "amount": 100.00,
  "currency": "USD",
  "eventTimestamp": "2026-06-26T16:00:00Z"
}

### 8d. Balance -> expect 120.00 (100 - 30 + 50) regardless of submit order
GET {{accountUrl}}/accounts/{{outOfOrderAcct}}/balance

### 8e. Event list -> sorted by eventTimestamp (T1, T2, T3)
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/events?account={{outOfOrderAcct}}

###############################################################################
# C. Error scenarios
###############################################################################

### 9. Validation failure — negative amount -> 400 ProblemDetails (includes traceId)
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/events
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "eventId": "evt-bad-9001",
  "accountId": "{{accountId}}",
  "type": "CREDIT",
  "amount": -5.00,
  "currency": "USD",
  "eventTimestamp": "2026-06-26T16:10:00Z"
}

### 10. Unknown event type -> 400
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/events
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "eventId": "evt-bad-9002",
  "accountId": "{{accountId}}",
  "type": "TRANSFER",
  "amount": 10.00,
  "currency": "USD",
  "eventTimestamp": "2026-06-26T16:11:00Z"
}

###############################################################################
# D. Optional — Swagger UI (Development environment; enabled in docker-compose)
###############################################################################

### Gateway Swagger
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/swagger/index.html

### Account Service Swagger
GET {{accountUrl}}/swagger/index.html

###############################################################################
# E. Observability — logs, traceId, distributed tracing (~2 min)
#
# Before E1: open a second terminal and tail service logs:
#   docker compose logs -f event-gateway account-service
# OR watch the dotnet run terminals if running locally.
#
# Look for: JSON logs with "TraceId", "ServiceName", structured fields.
# OpenTelemetry spans/metrics also export to the console in Development.
###############################################################################

### E1. Submit a NEW event while watching logs — same TraceId on Gateway + Account
# Use a unique eventId so this works even after section A.
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/events
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "eventId": "evt-obs-trace-001",
  "accountId": "acct-obs-demo",
  "type": "CREDIT",
  "amount": 25.00,
  "currency": "USD",
  "eventTimestamp": "2026-06-26T19:00:00Z",
  "metadata": { "source": "observability-demo" }
}

### E2. traceId in API error response — inspect JSON body field "traceId"
# (Same as step 9; re-run to show correlation id returned to clients.)
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/events
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "eventId": "evt-obs-bad-001",
  "accountId": "{{accountId}}",
  "type": "CREDIT",
  "amount": -1.00,
  "currency": "USD",
  "eventTimestamp": "2026-06-26T19:05:00Z"
}

### E3. Optional — prove trace propagation via automated test
#   dotnet test tests/EventLedger.IntegrationTests --filter TracePropagation

###############################################################################
# F. Optional — Graceful degradation (run AFTER section A)
#
# Prerequisites: Section A completed — Gateway has persisted events in gateway.db.
#
# Stop Account Service:
#   docker compose stop account-service
# OR stop the local dotnet process on port 8081.
#
# When finished, restart:
#   docker compose start account-service
###############################################################################

@degradeEventId = evt-degrade-001

### F1. POST /events while Account Service is down -> 503 ProblemDetails, event NOT stored
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/events
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "eventId": "{{degradeEventId}}",
  "accountId": "{{accountId}}",
  "type": "CREDIT",
  "amount": 99.00,
  "currency": "USD",
  "eventTimestamp": "2026-06-26T20:00:00Z",
  "metadata": { "source": "degradation-demo" }
}

### F2. Confirm degraded POST was not persisted -> 404 Not Found
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/events/{{degradeEventId}}

### F3. GET stored event from section A still works (Gateway local DB only)
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/events/{{creditEventId}}

### F4. Balance query fails — connection refused (Account Service unreachable)
GET {{accountUrl}}/accounts/{{accountId}}/balance

### F5. Restart Account Service when done
#   docker compose start account-service
# OR restart local dotnet on :8081, then re-run 0b health check.

